  "title": "Customer Financial Insight",
  "description": "•    Customer financial insights refer to the analysis and understanding of the financial aspects related to customer interactions and behaviors;  Customer Position SD is the basis for deriving financial insights is three discrete viewpoints. One is the customer's cash flows (i.e. patterns of money flowing in and out of their account), Two is credit (i.e. the current and permissable/target level of loans and deposits based on their creditworthiness). Three is their wealth/collateral position (i.e. longer term investments, property, retirement funds etc. that can be used as collateral against lending if needed)",
